org.ow2.proactive.resourcemanager.common.event

Class RMNodeEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ow2.proactive.resourcemanager.common.event.RMEvent
      • org.ow2.proactive.resourcemanager.common.event.RMNodeEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<RMEvent>

    @PublicAPI
public final class RMNodeEvent
extends RMEvent
    This class implements Event object related to an RMNode This immutable event object is thrown to all Resource Manager Monitors to inform them about a Node's state modification.

    This event can be:

    • a new Node acquisition.
    • a node becoming free.
    • a node becoming busy.
    • a node becoming to release.
    • a node becoming to down.
    • a node removed from the Resource Manager.
    An RMNodeSourceEvent contains all information about its related RMNode.
    Since:
    ProActive Scheduling 0.9
    See Also:
    RMMonitoring, Serialized Form
